Ask Desiderata is glad to present in Israel original masterpieces of engraving art.
There are more then 1 000 engravings at an affordable price in our collection, including
woodprint, steel engravings, eau-forte, lithography and cromolithography. Our goal is
to provide this part of culture to people, through understanding, that real history and real
art can be owned by anyone who are really interested on.
Engravings in our collection are 100% genuine, maded by publishers and private
masters in XVIII-XX Centuries. Prices are negotiable and generally not high, depending
on circulation of print or condition of image. Origin of engravings is guaranteed by expert
Michael Klimoff -- arts and books expert with more than 30 years experience of search,
valuation and selling antiques.
We can offer you more valuable masterpieces of engraving art, such as original
pieces maded by Hermann Struck, Max Liebermann, Charles W. Wilson e.t.c., that can
refill your existing or new born collection. In the same time we are looking for new
partners and connections, that can help us to provide our bussiness and knowledge.
There are weekly presentation of our collection in openspace fleamarkets in Israel,
that you can join to:
- every Thursday, Fleamarket on Krause street, Netanya, from 08:00 til 16:00.
- every Friday, Fleamarket on Dizengoff square, Tel-Aviv, from 08:00 til 16:00.
